verses.text_plain: And the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, set thy face against Gog, the land of Magog, the chief prince of Meshech and Tubal, and prophesy against him,
verses.verse_html:
2Son of man, set thy face against Gog, the land of Magog, the chief prince of Meshech and Tubal, and prophesy against him, ▼
▼ the chief…: or, prince of the chief

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the chief…: or, prince of the chief
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the chief…: or, prince of the chief

verses.text_plain: And say, Thus saith the Lord God; Behold, I am against thee, O Gog, the chief prince of Meshech and Tubal:
verses.verse_html: 3And say, Thus saith the Lord God; Behold, I am against thee, O Gog, the chief prince of Meshech and Tubal:

verses.text_plain: And I will turn thee back, and put hooks into thy jaws, and I will bring thee forth, and all thine army, horses and horsemen, all of them clothed with all sorts of armour, even a great company with bucklers and shields, all of them handling swords:
verses.verse_html: 4And I will turn thee back, and put hooks into thy jaws, and I will bring thee forth, and all thine army, horses and horsemen, all of them clothed with all sorts of armour, even a great company with bucklers and shields, all of them handling swords:

tokens.text: And I will turn thee back
and I will bring thee forth

verses.text_plain: Persia, Ethiopia, and Libya with them; all of them with shield and helmet:
verses.verse_html:
5Persia, Ethiopia, and Libya with them; all of them with shield and helmet: ▼
▼ Libya: or, Phut

tokens.text: with them; all of them with shield

verses.text_plain: Gomer, and all his bands; the house of Togarmah of the north quarters, and all his bands: and many people with thee.
verses.verse_html: 6Gomer, and all his bands; the house of Togarmah of the north quarters, and all his bands: and many people with thee.

verses.text_plain: Be thou prepared, and prepare for thyself, thou, and all thy company that are assembled unto thee, and be thou a guard unto them.
verses.verse_html: 7Be thou prepared, and prepare for thyself, thou, and all thy company that are assembled unto thee, and be thou a guard unto them.

tokens.text: for thyself, thou, and all thy company
unto thee, and be thou a guard

verses.text_plain: After many days thou shalt be visited: in the latter years thou shalt come into the land that is brought back from the sword, and is gathered out of many people, against the mountains of Israel, which have been always waste: but it is brought forth out of the nations, and they shall dwell safely all of them.
verses.verse_html: 8After many days thou shalt be visited: in the latter years thou shalt come into the land that is brought back from the sword, and is gathered out of many people, against the mountains of Israel, which have been always waste: but it is brought forth out of the nations, and they shall dwell safely all of them.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt ascend and come like a storm, thou shalt be like a cloud to cover the land, thou, and all thy bands, and many people with thee.
verses.verse_html: 9Thou shalt ascend and come like a storm, thou shalt be like a cloud to cover the land, thou, and all thy bands, and many people with thee.

tokens.text: thou shalt be like a cloud

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord God; It shall also come to pass, that at the same time shall things come into thy mind, and thou shalt think an evil thought:
verses.verse_html:
10Thus saith the Lord God; It shall also come to pass, that at the same time shall things come into thy mind, and thou shalt think an evil thought: ▼
▼ think…: or, conceive a mischievous purpose

footnotes.body_text: ▼ think…: or, conceive a mischievous purpose
footnotes.body_html: ▼ think…: or, conceive a mischievous purpose

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt say, I will go up to the land of unwalled villages; I will go to them that are at rest, that dwell safely, all of them dwelling without walls, and having neither bars nor gates,
verses.verse_html:
11And thou shalt say, I will go up to the land of unwalled villages; I will go to them that are at rest, that dwell safely, all of them dwelling without walls, and having neither bars nor gates, ▼
▼ safely: or, confidently

tokens.text: to them that are at rest

verses.text_plain: To take a spoil, and to take a prey; to turn thine hand upon the desolate places that are now inhabited, and upon the people that are gathered out of the nations, which have gotten cattle and goods, that dwell in the midst of the land.
verses.verse_html:
12To take a spoil, and to take a prey; to turn thine hand upon the desolate places that are now inhabited, and upon the people that are gathered out of the nations, which have gotten cattle and goods, that dwell in the midst of the land. ▼
▼ To take…: Heb. To spoil the spoil, and to prey the prey
 , ▼
▼ midst: Heb. navel

footnotes.body_text: ▼ To take…: Heb. To spoil the spoil, and to prey the prey
footnotes.body_html: ▼ To take…: Heb. To spoil the spoil, and to prey the prey

verses.text_plain: Sheba, and Dedan, and the merchants of Tarshish, with all the young lions thereof, shall say unto thee, Art thou come to take a spoil? hast thou gathered thy company to take a prey? to carry away silver and gold, to take away cattle and goods, to take a great spoil?
verses.verse_html: 13Sheba, and Dedan, and the merchants of Tarshish, with all the young lions thereof, shall say unto thee, Art thou come to take a spoil? hast thou gathered thy company to take a prey? to carry away silver and gold, to take away cattle and goods, to take a great spoil?

verses.text_plain: Therefore, son of man, prophesy and say unto Gog, Thus saith the Lord God; In that day when my people of Israel dwelleth safely, shalt thou not know it?
verses.verse_html: 14Therefore, son of man, prophesy and say unto Gog, Thus saith the Lord God; In that day when my people of Israel dwelleth safely, shalt thou not know it?

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt come from thy place out of the north parts, thou, and many people with thee, all of them riding upon horses, a great company, and a mighty army:
verses.verse_html: 15And thou shalt come from thy place out of the north parts, thou, and many people with thee, all of them riding upon horses, a great company, and a mighty army:

tokens.text: with thee, all of them riding

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt come up against my people of Israel, as a cloud to cover the land; it shall be in the latter days, and I will bring thee against my land, that the heathen may know me, when I shall be sanctified in thee, O Gog, before their eyes.
verses.verse_html: 16And thou shalt come up against my people of Israel, as a cloud to cover the land; it shall be in the latter days, and I will bring thee against my land, that the heathen may know me, when I shall be sanctified in thee, O Gog, before their eyes.

tokens.text: it shall be in the latter
me, when I shall be sanctified

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord God; Art thou he of whom I have spoken in old time by my servants the prophets of Israel, which prophesied in those days many years that I would bring thee against them?
verses.verse_html:
17Thus saith the Lord God; Art thou he of whom I have spoken in old time by my servants the prophets of Israel, which prophesied in those days many years that I would bring thee against them? ▼
▼ by: Heb. by the hand of

tokens.text: thou he of whom I have spoken

footnotes.body_text: ▼ by: Heb. by the hand of
footnotes.body_html: ▼ by: Heb. by the hand of

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass at the same time when Gog shall come against the land of Israel, saith the Lord God, that my fury shall come up in my face.
verses.verse_html: 18And it shall come to pass at the same time when Gog shall come against the land of Israel, saith the Lord God, that my fury shall come up in my face.

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass at the same time

verses.text_plain: For in my jealousy and in the fire of my wrath have I spoken, Surely in that day there shall be a great shaking in the land of Israel;
verses.verse_html: 19For in my jealousy and in the fire of my wrath have I spoken, Surely in that day there shall be a great shaking in the land of Israel;

verses.text_plain: So that the fishes of the sea, and the fowls of the heaven, and the beasts of the field, and all creeping things that creep upon the earth, and all the men that are upon the face of the earth, shall shake at my presence, and the mountains shall be thrown down, and the steep places shall fall, and every wall shall fall to the ground.
verses.verse_html:
20So that the fishes of the sea, and the fowls of the heaven, and the beasts of the field, and all creeping things that creep upon the earth, and all the men that are upon the face of the earth, shall shake at my presence, and the mountains shall be thrown down, and the steep places shall fall, and every wall shall fall to the ground. ▼
▼ steep…: or, towers, or, stairs

footnotes.body_html: ▼ steep…: or, towers, or, stairs

verses.text_plain: And I will call for a sword against him throughout all my mountains, saith the Lord God: every man’s sword shall be against his brother.
verses.verse_html: 21And I will call for a sword against him throughout all my mountains, saith the Lord God: every man’s sword shall be against his brother.

tokens.text: against him throughout all my mountains

verses.text_plain: And I will plead against him with pestilence and with blood; and I will rain upon him, and upon his bands, and upon the many people that are with him, an overflowing rain, and great hailstones, fire, and brimstone.
verses.verse_html: 22And I will plead against him with pestilence and with blood; and I will rain upon him, and upon his bands, and upon the many people that are with him, an overflowing rain, and great hailstones, fire, and brimstone.

tokens.text: upon him, and upon his bands

verses.text_plain: Thus will I magnify myself, and sanctify myself; and I will be known in the eyes of many nations, and they shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 23Thus will I magnify myself, and sanctify myself; and I will be known in the eyes of many nations, and they shall know that I am the Lord.

tokens.text: myself; and I will be known
